In Belgium, on 19 April 2021, a new "Closure and Regulation of Schools" policy was announced which was effective until 20 April 2023:  
- Nursery education, primary education, special needs secondary education, the first stage of secondary education and the system of ‘learning and working’: full-time face-to-face education;  
- 2nd and 3rd stage of secondary education: 50% face-to-face education;  - Higher Education: physical presence on campus 1 day/week. Exams can take place in person. If the infection rates evolve favorably and after an assessment by the Ministers of Education which will be submitted to the Consultative Committee, full-time secondary education can resume from 3 May, 2021.

