If the person returns from an orange zone , it is a quarantine 
is recommended. However, this recommendation should be taken seriously, especially if the person returning from an orange zone has had high-risk contacts;

The Expat Welcome Desk informs expats in Brussels about the latest measures taken in Belgium to limit the spread of Covid-19 from October 26, 2022. Quarantine procedure: When developing symptoms:
Self-isolate for 7 days and contact a doctor to arrange for a test;
If the patient tests positive, remain in quarantine for 7 days;
If the patient tests negative, he may end quarantine after the clinical resolution of symptoms.
Asymptomatic individuals : Who had close contact with an infected person should; who return from a red zone have mandatory 10 days quarantine.

