Belgium, 23 March 2020. 

All commercial establishments and stores remained closed, with the exception of: 
- food stores, including night shops;
- food stores for animals;
- pharmacies;
- bookstores and libraries; 
- petrol stations and fuel suppliers;
- hairdressers, who cannot receive than one client at a time and by appointment.

Markets are banned, except for essential stalls of food supply to areas without commercial food infrastructure.
The practice of sales and discounts are prohibited.

The necessary measures must be taken to ensure compliance with social distancing rules, in particular maintaining a distance of 1.5 meter between each person. These measures apply to all activities mentioned in this order.

The measures prescribed by this Order apply until 5 April 2020 included.

