Belgium, 29 October 2020.

Hotels, Restaurants, Cafes (HoReCa) and drinking establishments are closed, except to offer take-out and delivery meals and non-alcoholic beverages to take away until 10 p.m. at the latest. Meals can be offered to take away and/or deliver together with alcoholic beverages up to 8 p.m.

For HoReCa activities permitted by the Decree, the following specific conditions for accepting clients apply:
(1) the tables are arranged in such a way as to guarantee a distance between the tables of at least 1.5 meters, unless the tables are separated by a plexiglass wall or an equivalent alternative, with a minimum height of 1.8 meters;
(2) no more than 4 people can be accommodated at one table;
(3) only seats at the table are allowed;
(4) everyone should stay seated at their tables;
(5) wearing a mask is mandatory for staff;
(6) bar service is prohibited;
(7) the customer's contact details at each table, which may be limited to a phone number or email address, are recorded upon arrival and stored, in accordance with the requirements of personal data protection, for 14 calendar days to facilitate any subsequent search for contacts. Customers who refuse to provide their contact information will be denied access to the establishment upon arrival. These contact details cannot be used for purposes other than fighting COVID-19, and they must be deleted after 14 calendar days.

This order enters into force on October 29 2020.

